title: Aggregation of blood platelets by adrenaline and its uptake.
abstract: This study investigates the aggregation of blood platelets by adrenaline and its uptake. The research was conducted in the field of biochemical pharmacology.

title: Formate assay in body fluids: application in methanol poisoning.
abstract: The paper describes a formate assay method used for analyzing body fluids. The assay's utility is demonstrated in the context of methanol poisoning.

title: Clonal hematopoiesis and blood-cancer risk inferred from blood DNA sequence.
journal: The New England journal of medicine
abstract: This research explores the link between clonal hematopoiesis and blood cancer risk by analyzing blood DNA sequences. The study infers this relationship from genomic data.

title: Delineation of the intimate details of the backbone conformation of pyridine nucleotide coenzymes in aqueous solution.
abstract: The study focuses on detailing the backbone conformation of pyridine nucleotide coenzymes in an aqueous solution. It was investigated through biochemical and biophysical research methods.

title: Issues in adult blood cancer survivorship care.
abstract: This paper discusses various issues related to survivorship care for adults who have had blood cancer. It addresses these issues from an oncology nursing perspective.

title: Metal substitutions incarbonic anhydrase: a halide ion probe study.
abstract: The research examines the effects of metal substitutions in carbonic anhydrase, utilizing a halide ion probe. The work involves biochemical and biophysical research methods.

title: Multi-Target Cytotoxic Actions of Flavonoids in Blood Cancer Cells.
journal: Asian Pacific journal of cancer prevention : APJCP
abstract: This study investigates the multi-target cytotoxic actions of flavonoids in blood cancer cells. It explores the potential of flavonoids as agents in cancer prevention.

title: Effect of chloroquine on cultured fibroblasts: release of lysosomal hydrolases and inhibition of their uptake.
abstract: The paper explores the effect of chloroquine on cultured fibroblasts, specifically looking at the release of lysosomal hydrolases and the inhibition of their uptake. The research was carried out using biochemical and biophysical methods.

title: Diagnosis and classification of hematologic malignancies on the basis of genetics.
abstract: This paper discusses the diagnosis and classification of hematologic malignancies by genetic information. It highlights the role of genetics in understanding and categorizing these cancers.

title: Atomic models for the polypeptide backbones of myohemerythrin and hemerythrin.
abstract: The study presents atomic models for the polypeptide backbones of myohemerythrin and hemerythrin. The models were developed using biochemical and biophysical research methods.
